  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When the last message in a chat contains a long address it overlaps the next chat when that chat is clicked: \r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/34744396-594fb530-f58d-11e7-9b81-8f7e890c2506.png)\r\n\r\nIn this example the overlapping text appears only while clicking \"Console\" chat.\r\n  \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nFirst chat should not overlap the next one. \r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nIf a first chat contains a long message it overlaps the next one when that chat is clicked. \r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Open Chats tab\r\n- Open first chat and send a long location message\r\n- Go back to Chats\r\n- Long click on the second chat. It should be overlapped by the first chat as shown in the screenshot.\r\n\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.12 (TestFlight)\r\n* Operating System: iOS\r\n* Tested on: iPhone 6, iOS 11.2.1\r\n* Related to: https://github.com/status-im/status-react/issues/1436\r\n  ",
